The paper discusses a model for the evolution of helpfulness votes in online communities, which involves social processes and biases. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including social computing (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the use of Amazon product reviews and StackExchange forums as datasets suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-field of social informatics (cs.SI).
